Let’s talk about the powerrrr of getting a new hairstyle ! Every now and then I unlock a look that gives me the perfect shift of energy & always right when I need it 💫

 I’ve noticed more states “considering” the Crown Act & I really hope that one day soon (immediately?) the government will understand and acknowledge that our natural hair  is none of their business, how we style it is a form is self expression very personal to us, that there is no world in which anyone outside of our bodies should have a say on it. 

( I’ve been lowkey making all of my clients watch this 😅 ) season 1 episode 3 of random acts of flyness they portrayed the stereotypes of what “good” & “bad” hair is in the black community and how we can be free of those stereotypes and live in & love our hair and all of its power & I eat that episode up every time lmao ( this is me telling you to watch it because I stg it’s the most relatable , funny , & uplifting shit ever ..🤣)

I’ve grown a lot over the last few years but especially during my Time in New York. When  I first set out on my own 4 years ago, I was escaping, and with no real thought-out destination or goals just the short-term idea of survival. Everything I did was tied to survival, modeling, braiding, etc. I had no passion for what I was doing, and it became a strict means to live. I eventually got to the point where I realized the trauma I was trying to escape from was still being carried with me, by me every day and my attachment to it was stopping me from being able to give something to life, and since I wasn’t sowing I wasn’t reaping anything. New York gave me the space, and simultaneously the closeness to find my presence, and passion, and dig into who I am instead of what’s happened to me. I’ve found my voice so get used to it :). I am here!  I have dreams and goals that I will see through. I’m assertive, confident, & 1000% 
“Tre’Nae”
